---
import MainLayout from "@/layouts/MainLayout.astro";
import SEO from "@/components/SEO/index.astro";
import MainPageTitle from "@/components/MainPageTitle/index.astro";
import bgImage from "@/assets/images/events.jpeg";
import Prose from "@/components/Prose/index.astro";
---

<MainLayout>
  <SEO
    slot="seo"
    title="Privacy Policy"
    description="Learn about how Fork it! Community collects, uses, and protects your personal data. Understand your rights and our GDPR-compliant practices."
  />
  <MainPageTitle
    title="Privacy Policy"
    subtitle="Your privacy matters to us"
    imageSrc={bgImage}
  />
  <section class="m-auto max-w-7xl px-4 py-16">
    <Prose>
      <p class="text-sm opacity-60">Last updated: February 12, 2026</p>

      <h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h2>
      <p>
        Fork it! Community ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting
        your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use,
        disclose, and safeguard your information when you visit our website.
      </p>

      <h2 id="privacy-first-approach">Privacy-First Approach</h2>
      <div>
        <p>Our website does not maintain its own user database.</p>
        <p>
          We rely on trusted third-party services to collect and store personal
          data on our behalf:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Luma</strong> for event management</li>
          <li><strong>Brevo</strong> for newsletter subscriptions</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Analytics and marketing tools are enabled only after you have given
          your explicit consent.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h2 id="data-controller">Data Controller</h2>
      <p>
        The data controller responsible for the processing of personal data is:
      </p>
      <p>
        <strong>Fork it! Community</strong><br />
        Email: <a href="mailto:contact@forkit.community"
          >contact@forkit.community</a
        >
      </p>
      <p>
        Fork it! Community determines the purposes and means of processing
        personal data described in this Privacy Policy.
      </p>

      <h2 id="information-we-collect">Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        We collect information that you provide directly to us and information
        that is automatically collected when you use our website.
      </p>

      <h3>Information You Provide</h3>

      <h4>Event Registration (via Luma)</h4>
      <p>When you register for an event, you may provide:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Name</li>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Phone number</li>
        <li>
          Cryptocurrency wallet addresses (Ethereum / Solana, if provided)
        </li>
        <li>Responses to custom registration questions</li>
        <li>Event attendance and check-in data</li>
        <li>Payment and ticketing information (if applicable)</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Newsletter Subscription (via Brevo)</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Email address</li>
        <li>Communication preferences</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Communications</h4>
      <p>Any other information you voluntarily choose to provide.</p>

      <h3>Automatically Collected Information</h3>
      <p>
        When you visit our website, certain information may be collected through
        cookies and similar tracking technologies, only with your consent for
        analytics and marketing purposes:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Device and browser information</li>
        <li>IP address and approximate location data</li>
        <li>Pages visited and time spent on pages</li>
        <li>Referring website addresses</li>
        <li>Interaction with website features</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Information We Do Not Collect</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Search Queries:</strong> Our website search functionality is client-side
          only and does not track or store your search queries.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>User Accounts:</strong> We do not maintain user accounts or authentication
          systems on our website.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>First-Party Database:</strong> We do not store personal data in
          our own database.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>All personal data is managed by our third-party partners.</p>

      <h2 id="purposes-and-legal-bases">
        Purposes and Legal Bases for Processing
      </h2>
      <p>
        We process personal data only when a valid legal basis applies, in
        accordance with the GDPR:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Event registration management</strong><br />
          <ul>
            <li>Legal basis: performance of a service requested by the user</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Newsletter and community communications</strong><br />
          <ul>
            <li>Legal basis: consent</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Website analytics and user experience improvement</strong><br
          />
          <ul>
            <li>Legal basis: consent</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Marketing performance measurement (Meta platforms)</strong><br
          />
          <ul>
            <li>Legal basis: consent</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Website security and abuse prevention</strong><br />
          <ul>
            <li>Legal basis: legitimate interest</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Compliance with legal obligations</strong><br />
          <ul>
            <li>Legal basis: legal obligation</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="cookies-and-tracking">Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
      <p>
        We use cookies and similar technologies to ensure proper website
        functionality and, with your consent, for analytics and marketing
        purposes. You can manage your cookie preferences using our Cookie
        Settings tool available in the footer of this page.
      </p>

      <h3>Types of Cookies We Use</h3>

      <h4>Essential Cookies</h4>
      <p>
        These cookies are necessary for the website to function properly. They
        enable core functionality such as security, consent management, and
        accessibility features.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>forkit-consent:</strong> Stores your cookie consent preferences
          for 365 days.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Analytics Cookies</h4>
      <p>
        We use analytics services to understand how visitors use our website.
        This helps us improve content and user experience. These cookies require
        your explicit consent.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Vercel Analytics:</strong> Collects anonymous usage data to help
          us understand visitor behavior and improve website performance.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Microsoft Clarity:</strong> We partner with Microsoft Clarity to
          capture how you use and interact with our website through behavioral metrics,
          heatmaps, and session replay to improve and market our products/services.
          Website usage data is captured using first and third-party cookies and
          other tracking technologies to determine the popularity of products/services
          and online activity. Additionally, we use this information for site optimization
          and fraud/security purposes. For more information about how Microsoft collects
          and uses your data, visit the <a
            href="https://www.microsoft.com/privacy/privacystatement"
            >Microsoft Privacy Statement</a
          >.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Marketing Cookies</h4>
      <p>
        These cookies track your activity to deliver personalized advertisements
        and measure campaign effectiveness. These cookies require your explicit
        consent.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Meta Pixel:</strong> Used to measure advertising effectiveness,
          understand which content resonates with our community, and improve our
          marketing campaigns on Meta platforms (Facebook, Instagram).
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="third-party-services">Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        We use trusted third-party services that may process personal data in
        accordance with their own privacy policies:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Luma</strong> &ndash; event management</li>
        <li><strong>Brevo</strong> &ndash; email marketing</li>
        <li><strong>Meta</strong> &ndash; advertising and analytics</li>
        <li><strong>Vercel</strong> &ndash; website analytics</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        These providers act as data processors or, where applicable, independent
        data controllers, in compliance with applicable data protection laws.
      </p>

      <h2 id="data-retention">Data Retention</h2>
      <p>
        Personal data is retained only for as long as necessary to fulfill the
        purposes described in this Privacy Policy:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Cookie consent preferences:</strong> 365 days
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Event registration data:</strong> retained according to Luma's
          retention policies
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Newsletter data:</strong> retained by Brevo until you unsubscribe
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Analytics data:</strong> retained according to Vercel and Meta
          retention policies
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="data-security">Data Security</h2>
      <p>
        We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to
        protect your personal information against unauthorized access,
        alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of
        transmission over the internet is entirely secure.
      </p>

      <h2 id="international-transfers">International Data Transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other
        than your country of residence. When applicable, appropriate safeguards
        are implemented in accordance with the GDPR.
      </p>

      <h2 id="your-rights">Your Rights Under GDPR</h2>
      <p>
        If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), you have the
        right to:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Access your personal data</li>
        <li>Request rectification of inaccurate data</li>
        <li>Request erasure of your data</li>
        <li>Restrict processing</li>
        <li>Request data portability</li>
        <li>Object to processing</li>
        <li>Withdraw your consent at any time</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You may exercise these rights by contacting us at: <a
          href="mailto:contact@forkit.community">contact@forkit.community</a
        >
      </p>

      <h2 id="right-to-lodge-complaint">Right to Lodge a Complaint</h2>
      <p>
        If you believe that your data protection rights have been violated, you
        have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.
      </p>
      <p>
        For France, this authority is:<br />
        <strong>CNIL</strong> &ndash; Commission Nationale de l'Informatique et des
        Libert√©s: <a
          href="https://www.cnil.fr"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">www.cnil.fr</a
        >
      </p>

      <h2 id="changes-to-policy">Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. We will notify you
        of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page and
        updating the "Last updated" date.
      </p>

      <h2 id="contact-us">Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or wish to exercise
        your data protection rights, please contact us:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Email: <a href="mailto:contact@forkit.community"
            >contact@forkit.community</a
          >
        </li>
        <li>
          Website: <a href="https://forkit.community">forkit.community</a>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </Prose>
  </section>
</MainLayout>
